itle>   Thurgadin gate potions</span><hr size=1> In case anyone is interested, here is a short walk-through on making Thurgadin gate potions.  These are needed for melees for a zone like HS when we don't have a druid or wizzy; they're also just darn convenient (I just used one the other day to get from my camp in Dulak with no fuss).<br>
<br>
The pieces you'll need can be found in either Crystal Caverns or Velketor's Labyrinth.  I've been taking a couple hours every few weeks and blowing through CC to collect enough parts for a number of potions so that I can just make a new one when I use one up.  For each potion, the drops you'll need are: 3 crystalline silks (off spiders in CC or Velk's), a small brick of velium (off orc miners in CC or spiders in Velk's), and 2 small pieces of velium (same as bricks).  You'll also need 2 glass shards and a HQ firing sheet, which are on any pottery vendors; you can find them on vendors in the bank building in Thurgadin.<br>
<br>
Combine the 3 crystalline silks and the small brick of velium with 2 glass shards in a pottery wheel; then take that unfired vial and combine it with a HQ firing sheet in the kiln.  I think the trivial for this is around 122 pottery or so; pottery is fairly easy to raise tho, just lots of clicking.  The fired vial is no drop, but it isn't lore (this is the only step where it isn't lore I think), so you can make a bunch to have ready for the final combine (I have a stack of small pieces of velium and 5 or 6 fired vials in the bank ready to go).<br>
<br>
The final combine is done in a purifier box, which you need to get from Frundle Frenkler in Thurgadin.  Coming from GD, turn left in Thurgadin and head toward the library; Frundle will be in a building on your left just before you get there.  Make sure you have an open slot for a container, then say to Frundle &quot;What velium vapors?&quot;  Combine the vial with the 2 small pieces of velium (unstacked) and you have your potion.  Cast time is 10 seconds, and it drops you off right near the bridges at the entrance in Thurgadin. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=445044" target="top">Xenophon</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, 56 Paladin<br>
